1
00:00:36,500 --> 00:00:38,100
<i>Hazel's serious
about her accusation.</i>

2
00:00:38,233 --> 00:00:41,200
<i>She really believes
Coleen killed Jessica.</i>

3
00:00:41,333 --> 00:00:43,900
<i> Let her accuse all she wants.</i>

4
00:00:44,033 --> 00:00:45,400
<i>The truth will eventually
come out,</i>

5
00:00:45,533 --> 00:00:47,200
<i>and it will prove that
our daughter is innocent.</i>

6
00:00:47,333 --> 00:00:49,867
<i>They found an abandoned
vehicle in Fairview.</i>

7
00:00:50,000 --> 00:00:51,167
<i>The police can't confirm it yet,</i>

8
00:00:51,300 --> 00:00:53,167
<i>but there's a dent
in the bumper.</i>

9
00:00:53,300 --> 00:00:56,367
<i>Right where the footage
showed Jessica getting hit.</i>

10
00:00:56,500 --> 00:00:57,933
<i> There will only be justice</i>

11
00:00:58,067 --> 00:00:59,300
<i>when that Coleen girl
is behind bars.</i>

12
00:00:59,433 --> 00:01:01,267
<i> That's why I swear, dear.</i>

13
00:01:01,400 --> 00:01:03,400
<i>I won't let Coleen
have a moment of peace.</i>

14
00:01:03,533 --> 00:01:04,800
<i> Dad, I'm sorry.</i>

15
00:01:04,933 --> 00:01:08,633
<i>I'm sorry you can't go
to my sister's funeral</i>

16
00:01:08,800 --> 00:01:10,167
<i> because of me.</i>

17
00:01:10,300 --> 00:01:12,200
<i> I'm so sorry, Dad.</i>

18
00:01:12,333 --> 00:01:13,367
<i> Sorry, Jessica.</i>

19
00:01:13,500 --> 00:01:16,533
<i>I hope you know
how much I love you.</i>

20
00:01:16,667 --> 00:01:19,067
<i>Because no matter what happens,
you're my child.</i>

21
00:01:19,200 --> 00:01:22,767
<i>Jessica, please forgive me,
my child.</i>

22
00:01:24,133 --> 00:01:27,433
<i>Why did you take Jessica away
from me so soon?</i>

23
00:01:27,567 --> 00:01:29,267
<i>You know how much I've suffered</i>

24
00:01:29,400 --> 00:01:33,367
<i>when I lost Jeff, Andeng,
and Coleen.</i>

25
00:01:33,500 --> 00:01:36,367
<i>And now that things were finally
starting to get better,</i>

26
00:01:36,500 --> 00:01:39,133
<i> you took Jessica away from me!</i>

27
00:01:45,633 --> 00:01:47,467
<i> It's Jessica, right?</i>

28
00:01:47,600 --> 00:01:48,433
<i> Yes.</i>

29
00:01:48,567 --> 00:01:49,433
<i> Please, calm down.</i>

30
00:01:49,567 --> 00:01:52,200
<i>I don't know why
Andrea called you.</i>

31
00:01:52,333 --> 00:01:55,033
<i>She said a lot
of hurtful things.</i>

32
00:01:55,167 --> 00:01:59,500
<i>But please, don't let her anger
at mom drag dad into it.</i>

33
00:01:59,633 --> 00:02:02,567
<i>I know I'm the result of what
mom and dad did to you,</i>

34
00:02:02,700 --> 00:02:03,600
<i> their mistake.</i>

35
00:02:03,733 --> 00:02:07,133
<i>And yet, you were so kind to me.</i>

36
00:02:07,267 --> 00:02:08,800
<i> Thank you so much.</i>

37
00:02:08,933 --> 00:02:14,967
<i>I feel loved and accepted
by a very special person</i>

38
00:02:15,133 --> 00:02:17,767
<i>who is in any way
not related to me.</i>

39
00:02:17,900 --> 00:02:19,400
<i> That person is Aunt Felma.</i>

40
00:02:19,533 --> 00:02:23,400
<i>I want to honor her
for her kindness.</i>

41
00:02:32,433 --> 00:02:35,400
<i>Jeffrey, why are you
still awake?</i>

42
00:02:35,533 --> 00:02:36,267
<i> Why are you talking to me?</i>

43
00:02:36,400 --> 00:02:37,433
<i> Are we even close?</i>

44
00:02:37,567 --> 00:02:38,267
<i> Sorry.</i>

45
00:02:38,400 --> 00:02:39,433
<i> Jessica!</i>

46
00:02:39,567 --> 00:02:39,900
<i> That's enough!</i>

47
00:02:40,033 --> 00:02:41,067
<i> Jessica!</i>

48
00:02:41,200 --> 00:02:42,333
<i>- Stay away!
- Enough!</i>

49
00:02:42,467 --> 00:02:43,167
<i> Outsider!</i>

50
00:02:43,300 --> 00:02:44,800
<i>Aren't you tired
of being bullied</i>

51
00:02:44,933 --> 00:02:46,600
<i> by your own children, Dad?</i>

52
00:02:46,733 --> 00:02:47,600
<i> Won't you stop?</i>

53
00:02:47,767 --> 00:02:48,900
<i>You weren't even part of this,
right?</i>

54
00:02:52,133 --> 00:02:53,167
<i>Jessica, let's go.
Let's go home.</i>

55
00:02:53,300 --> 00:02:54,500
<i> Let's just go straight home.</i>

56
00:02:54,633 --> 00:02:55,833
<i> I'll recover there.</i>

57
00:02:55,967 --> 00:02:59,467
<i>Dad, even if you feel fine,
you still need to see a doctor.</i>

58
00:02:59,600 --> 00:03:01,600
<i>Dad, please listen to my sister.</i>

59
00:03:01,733 --> 00:03:03,033
<i>Jessica, you're not
getting out of this car.</i>

60
00:03:03,167 --> 00:03:06,300
<i>You're staying with us.
We're going home together.</i>

61
00:03:15,633 --> 00:03:17,567
<i> I don't care about your dad.</i>

62
00:03:17,700 --> 00:03:20,833
<i>And please tell your
good-for-nothing mother</i>

63
00:03:21,000 --> 00:03:24,700
<i>that she disrespected my family
first when she stole my father.</i>

64
00:03:24,833 --> 00:03:26,000
<i> And you.</i>

65
00:03:26,133 --> 00:03:27,167
<i> Who are you, really?</i>

66
00:03:27,300 --> 00:03:30,467
<i>Mrs. Wilson's calling, Jessica.</i>

67
00:03:30,600 --> 00:03:33,467
<i>Andrea, please don't be mad
at Coleen.</i>

68
00:03:33,600 --> 00:03:36,000
<i>How many times do I have to tell
you, don't call me sister!</i>

69
00:03:36,133 --> 00:03:37,233
<i> And stop meddling.</i>

70
00:03:37,367 --> 00:03:38,867
<i>You're not part
of this family.</i>

71
00:03:39,000 --> 00:03:40,533
<i> Jessica is our guest.</i>

72
00:03:40,667 --> 00:03:43,867
<i> Guests are welcome here.</i>

73
00:03:44,000 --> 00:03:45,700
<i> But she isn't welcome.</i>

74
00:03:45,833 --> 00:03:47,600
<i> Jessica let me in.</i>

75
00:03:47,733 --> 00:03:48,600
<i> She hurried me.</i>

76
00:03:48,733 --> 00:03:50,433
<i> I don't know why.</i>

77
00:03:50,567 --> 00:03:52,433
<i>She pushed her down the stairs.</i>

78
00:03:52,567 --> 00:03:54,800
<i>I'm sorry, I couldn't stop her.</i>

79
00:03:54,967 --> 00:03:56,533
<i>You did nothing wrong, Jessica.</i>

80
00:03:56,667 --> 00:03:59,100
<i>But me, I've done so much wrong
to you.</i>

81
00:03:59,233 --> 00:04:01,033
<i>- I'm sorry.
- It's over.</i>

82
00:04:01,167 --> 00:04:02,533
<i> Let's forget about it.</i>

83
00:04:07,967 --> 00:04:10,200
<i>You're not even part
of this family!</i>

84
00:04:10,333 --> 00:04:13,367
<i>Good thing that I don't belong
to your family!</i>

85
00:04:13,500 --> 00:04:15,367
<i>Because I don't want to belong
to a family</i>

86
00:04:15,500 --> 00:04:17,633
<i>that's rude and doesn't know
how to forgive!</i>

87
00:04:17,767 --> 00:04:18,933
<i> And what will you do?</i>

88
00:04:19,067 --> 00:04:21,033
<i>Stop dad's annulment
with your mom?</i>

89
00:04:21,167 --> 00:04:22,500
<i> How dare you!</i>

90
00:04:24,500 --> 00:04:25,467
<i> I'm your sister, Coleen!</i>

91
00:04:25,600 --> 00:04:27,100
<i> I don't want you as my sister!</i>

92
00:04:27,233 --> 00:04:29,100
<i> I wish you'd just disappear</i>

93
00:04:29,267 --> 00:04:30,933
<i>so my family could
finally be happy!</i>

94
00:04:31,067 --> 00:04:31,967
<i>- Jessica, please!
- No!</i>

95
00:04:32,100 --> 00:04:33,333
<i>- Let me go!
- Jessica!</i>

96
00:04:33,467 --> 00:04:36,000
<i> Jessica!</i>

97
00:05:05,100 --> 00:05:06,967
You shameless people!

98
00:05:07,100 --> 00:05:08,467
How dare you!

99
00:05:10,600 --> 00:05:11,567
- You shameless people!
- Friend!

100
00:05:21,533 --> 00:05:25,367
<i>I wish this were
just a dream, dear.</i>

101
00:05:25,500 --> 00:05:27,233
<i>I wish that when I wake up
tomorrow...</i>

102
00:05:28,400 --> 00:05:30,067
<i> I'd still see you.</i>

103
00:05:32,700 --> 00:05:34,900
<i>I wish it were me
lying there, not you.</i>

104
00:05:36,800 --> 00:05:39,333
<i>Because I'm the reason
for all this pain.</i>

105
00:05:41,400 --> 00:05:43,800
<i>If I weren't here, everyone's
lives would be peaceful.</i>

106
00:05:45,167 --> 00:05:46,833
<i> It should've been me.</i>

107
00:05:46,967 --> 00:05:49,267
<i>I should've been
the one who died.</i>

108
00:05:57,733 --> 00:05:59,200
What do you think
you're doing?

109
00:05:59,333 --> 00:06:00,000
Hazel, come on.

110
00:06:00,133 --> 00:06:01,133
Don't! Stop!

111
00:06:01,267 --> 00:06:02,000
Let go of me!

112
00:06:02,133 --> 00:06:03,433
Let me go!

113
00:06:03,900 --> 00:06:07,667
Mrs. Cruz, please,
don't be the aggressor.

114
00:06:07,833 --> 00:06:10,767
We can't just come after them.

115
00:06:10,900 --> 00:06:12,533
You could be charged.

116
00:06:13,867 --> 00:06:15,700
If you want justice
for your daughter,

117
00:06:16,600 --> 00:06:18,267
let's do this through the law.

118
00:06:19,000 --> 00:06:20,433
Not through anger.

119
00:06:23,367 --> 00:06:28,200
Attorney, I no longer care
about your laws!

120
00:06:29,300 --> 00:06:31,433
What they did to me
was an insult!

121
00:06:34,900 --> 00:06:37,733
Only Manuel and I should
be mourning Jessica.

122
00:06:38,967 --> 00:06:40,367
Not them.
They don't belong here.

123
00:06:42,500 --> 00:06:43,367
Hazel...

124
00:06:43,500 --> 00:06:45,300
Didn't you forbid them
from coming?

125
00:06:47,267 --> 00:06:48,533
Yes.

126
00:06:49,233 --> 00:06:50,733
And I regret it.

127
00:06:52,067 --> 00:06:57,300
I thought Manuel would
still come to comfort me.

128
00:06:57,433 --> 00:06:58,800
But I never imagined...

129
00:07:00,900 --> 00:07:06,233
he'd sneak in with his
illegitimate family.

130
00:07:13,933 --> 00:07:16,400
So, friend,
what's your plan now?

131
00:07:17,200 --> 00:07:18,467
To make Coleen pay.

132
00:07:20,633 --> 00:07:22,267
And after that?

133
00:07:22,400 --> 00:07:24,367
You're flying back to Canada?

134
00:07:24,500 --> 00:07:26,667
There's nothing left
for me there, Alice.

135
00:07:28,433 --> 00:07:29,400
I'm staying here.

136
00:07:31,767 --> 00:07:33,100
I'll start working again.

137
00:07:35,867 --> 00:07:37,200
And I'm moving out.

138
00:07:38,933 --> 00:07:41,267
A townhouse, maybe.

139
00:07:41,400 --> 00:07:42,600
Not a condo this time.

140
00:07:43,700 --> 00:07:45,433
I already asked Maximo
to look for one.

141
00:07:47,500 --> 00:07:50,000
Wait, a whole house?

142
00:07:50,133 --> 00:07:51,933
Where will you get
the money for rent?

143
00:07:53,667 --> 00:07:56,367
Mr. and Mrs. Wilson are still
sending support.

144
00:07:57,967 --> 00:08:03,267
I already told them we won't be
going back to Canada for now.

145
00:08:04,433 --> 00:08:06,767
They didn't even take back
the money they gave

146
00:08:06,900 --> 00:08:08,300
for our plane tickets.

147
00:08:09,333 --> 00:08:10,467
So, I've saved enough.

148
00:08:11,267 --> 00:08:13,333
Then why a whole house?

149
00:08:14,600 --> 00:08:15,433
Alice...

150
00:08:17,000 --> 00:08:18,333
Because I'm preparing
for something.

151
00:08:21,933 --> 00:08:23,900
I'm preparing for
Manuel's return.

152
00:08:26,133 --> 00:08:27,600
Manuel's coming back, Alice.

153
00:08:30,600 --> 00:08:34,233
Friend, I know you're grieving.

154
00:08:34,367 --> 00:08:36,733
But don't be delusional.

155
00:08:36,867 --> 00:08:39,433
Why would Manuel come back?

156
00:08:39,567 --> 00:08:41,567
Jessica's gone.

157
00:08:41,700 --> 00:08:45,067
She was the only reason he
might've looked your way again.

158
00:08:46,833 --> 00:08:48,767
Just wait and see, Alice.

159
00:08:56,400 --> 00:08:58,533
Dad, I'll sleep here
in your room.

160
00:08:58,667 --> 00:09:00,033
So you won't be alone.

161
00:09:00,167 --> 00:09:01,100
Okay?

162
00:09:07,233 --> 00:09:08,200
Sir Manuel?

163
00:09:08,333 --> 00:09:10,267
Sir Manuel! You're home already!

164
00:09:10,400 --> 00:09:12,567
- Welcome home, Sir Manuel!
- Didang!

165
00:09:12,700 --> 00:09:13,767
It's all right, Didang.

166
00:09:13,900 --> 00:09:16,233
Thank you for welcoming
Manuel back.

167
00:09:16,367 --> 00:09:18,500
I'm sorry.

168
00:09:18,633 --> 00:09:19,633
Son, let me help you with that.

169
00:09:19,767 --> 00:09:20,900
No, Mom, it's fine.

170
00:09:21,033 --> 00:09:22,600
I can handle it. It's easy.

171
00:09:51,067 --> 00:09:52,400
<i> Come on, tell me.</i>

172
00:09:52,533 --> 00:09:53,800
<i> What's wrong?</i>

173
00:09:53,933 --> 00:09:54,967
<i> Dad...</i>

174
00:09:55,100 --> 00:09:56,467
<i> just hold me.</i>

175
00:09:56,600 --> 00:09:59,033
<i> Please don't let go.</i>

176
00:09:59,167 --> 00:10:02,100
<i>My baby girl just
wanted a hug.</i>

177
00:10:03,833 --> 00:10:05,800
<i> I love you so much, Dad.</i>

178
00:10:08,900 --> 00:10:10,533
<i> Dad, I love you.</i>

179
00:10:11,767 --> 00:10:13,967
<i>I love you so much, too,
sweetheart.</i>

180
00:10:27,400 --> 00:10:29,600
Ma'am...

181
00:10:29,733 --> 00:10:31,533
That's it...

182
00:10:31,667 --> 00:10:35,433
just like what I've
seen in the dramas.

183
00:10:35,600 --> 00:10:38,533
But it hurts so much more
when you see it in real life.

184
00:10:39,967 --> 00:10:43,467
Jessica, I'll miss you.

185
00:10:48,300 --> 00:10:49,533
Didang, stop crying now.

186
00:10:51,467 --> 00:10:52,367
Come on, let's go.

187
00:11:05,167 --> 00:11:07,833
Dad, I can't imagine your pain.

188
00:11:10,633 --> 00:11:12,033
I lost a child, too, yes.

189
00:11:14,967 --> 00:11:17,000
But I know where my Tetay is.

190
00:11:20,133 --> 00:11:21,567
I can visit her...

191
00:11:23,700 --> 00:11:24,967
I can still see her...

192
00:11:28,367 --> 00:11:29,767
I can hold her again.

193
00:11:33,300 --> 00:11:35,067
But yours, it's different.

194
00:11:41,433 --> 00:11:42,900
Dad, I'm here, okay?

195
00:11:48,467 --> 00:11:49,733
I won't leave you.

196
00:11:51,033 --> 00:11:54,333
If you ever need someone
to drink with, I'm here, okay?

197
00:11:54,467 --> 00:11:56,433
Just say the word,
we'll drink all night.

198
00:12:12,767 --> 00:12:14,467
<i>Didang, please bring this
to Coleen.</i>

199
00:12:14,600 --> 00:12:15,867
- Yes, Ma'am.
- I'll be there in a while.

200
00:12:16,300 --> 00:12:16,967
All right.

201
00:12:22,767 --> 00:12:24,033
Where's your dad?

202
00:12:24,467 --> 00:12:26,233
I called him already, but
he won't come out of his room.

203
00:12:28,567 --> 00:12:29,667
Call him again.

204
00:12:29,800 --> 00:12:31,467
I already went twice, Mom.

205
00:12:32,133 --> 00:12:33,367
He said he was not
in the mood to eat.

206
00:12:34,900 --> 00:12:36,367
Oh, no, he needs to eat.

207
00:12:37,300 --> 00:12:39,100
He's taking so many medicines.

208
00:12:40,633 --> 00:12:42,233
All right, Mom,
I'll go and call him.

209
00:12:50,400 --> 00:12:51,533
It was supposed to be our first
dinner together again

210
00:12:51,667 --> 00:12:52,800
as a complete family, right?

211
00:12:53,767 --> 00:12:55,300
It'll happen, son.

212
00:12:56,567 --> 00:12:57,933
When everything's okay.

213
00:12:59,167 --> 00:13:00,400
Yes, but...

214
00:13:01,733 --> 00:13:02,933
dad isn't the same anymore.

215
00:13:04,333 --> 00:13:05,667
Because Jessica's gone.

216
00:13:07,367 --> 00:13:09,267
We'll never be with her anymore.

217
00:13:24,033 --> 00:13:25,233
Dad, come on now.

218
00:13:26,233 --> 00:13:27,367
Please eat something.

219
00:13:29,933 --> 00:13:30,900
You need to eat, Dad.

220
00:13:31,033 --> 00:13:32,233
You're still recovering.

221
00:13:33,333 --> 00:13:34,667
You know, Andeng...

222
00:13:35,433 --> 00:13:38,633
It's so hard to accept that
your sister's gone.

223
00:13:39,267 --> 00:13:40,367
The only reason I managed

224
00:13:40,500 --> 00:13:42,200
to be away from you all
those years was...

225
00:13:43,367 --> 00:13:45,033
because of Jessica.

226
00:13:45,433 --> 00:13:49,267
When she was growing up,
I saw you in her.

227
00:13:50,800 --> 00:13:53,800
When she was a baby,

228
00:13:55,400 --> 00:13:57,967
she reminded me so much
of Coleen.

229
00:13:59,967 --> 00:14:04,867
But the older she got,
the more she became like you.

230
00:14:05,867 --> 00:14:10,467
Your hug, your sweetness...

231
00:14:12,133 --> 00:14:14,733
Everything about her
reminded me of you.

232
00:14:16,467 --> 00:14:20,300
Sometimes, I'd even call her
Andeng by mistake.

233
00:14:21,667 --> 00:14:24,067
I wish you'd spent
more time together.

234
00:14:24,200 --> 00:14:27,367
You'd have seen how alike
you really were.

235
00:14:29,933 --> 00:14:31,533
And I'm sure,

236
00:14:31,667 --> 00:14:32,933
you two would've gotten
along so well.

237
00:14:36,633 --> 00:14:37,800
I'm sorry, Dad.

238
00:15:09,167 --> 00:15:11,900
Mrs. Cruz, the case
you can file against Coleen...

239
00:15:13,467 --> 00:15:17,167
is reckless imprudence
resulting in homicide.

240
00:15:19,333 --> 00:15:23,400
If it's true that
she pushed Jessica.

241
00:15:25,767 --> 00:15:27,967
They think I'm just making
accusations, Attorney.

242
00:15:29,233 --> 00:15:32,267
But I know what I feel.

243
00:15:32,400 --> 00:15:34,333
I know Coleen pushed
my daughter.

244
00:15:34,500 --> 00:15:37,167
I can feel it,
a mother's instinct!

245
00:15:37,300 --> 00:15:40,333
Okay, if that's your conviction.

246
00:15:41,667 --> 00:15:43,333
But you know, Mrs. Cruz,

247
00:15:43,467 --> 00:15:47,900
mother's instinct isn't
admissible in the court of law.

248
00:15:48,033 --> 00:15:50,167
Mrs. Cruz, what we need
is evidence.

249
00:16:03,000 --> 00:16:04,833
You really have no shame,
Coleen.

250
00:16:04,967 --> 00:16:07,000
How dare you show
your face here.

251
00:16:09,367 --> 00:16:11,700
Mrs. Cruz!
Are we leaving now?

252
00:16:11,833 --> 00:16:13,833
<i>Oh, where are we supposed to go?
We just got here!</i>

253
00:16:24,700 --> 00:16:26,100
Mrs. Cruz, whatever plan
you've got in mind,

254
00:16:26,233 --> 00:16:27,500
don't go through with it!

255
00:16:54,200 --> 00:16:54,933
What?

256
00:16:56,233 --> 00:16:59,467
Now you know how it feels
to almost get hit by a car.

257
00:16:59,600 --> 00:17:02,700
You were just almost hit,
but did you see my daughter?

258
00:17:02,833 --> 00:17:03,800
She was thrown,

259
00:17:03,933 --> 00:17:04,833
and she died!

260
00:17:04,967 --> 00:17:06,133
Because of you!

261
00:17:07,167 --> 00:17:08,800
No, I didn't do anything wrong.

262
00:17:08,933 --> 00:17:10,233
What do you mean you didn't?

263
00:17:10,367 --> 00:17:12,467
- I swear, I didn't!
- It was your fault!

264
00:17:12,600 --> 00:17:13,467
It was your fault!

265
00:17:13,600 --> 00:17:15,000
It was your fault
my daughter's dead!

266
00:17:15,167 --> 00:17:16,367
- No.
- I won't forget that.

267
00:17:16,500 --> 00:17:17,867
I can never forgive you!

268
00:17:18,000 --> 00:17:20,300
- No! I didn't push Jessica!
- I'll never forgive you!

269
00:17:20,433 --> 00:17:21,433
- No!
- I didn't push Jessica!

270
00:17:21,567 --> 00:17:23,167
Please believe me!

271
00:17:23,300 --> 00:17:24,967
I didn't push my sister!

272
00:17:25,100 --> 00:17:26,900
- Please, I'm begging you.
- What...

273
00:17:27,033 --> 00:17:28,600
It was an accident!

274
00:17:28,733 --> 00:17:30,533
- Mrs. Cruz.
- I'll never believe you.

275
00:17:30,667 --> 00:17:31,900
- And I'll never forgive you.
- Please.

276
00:17:32,033 --> 00:17:33,800
- Do you understand?
- Mrs. Cruz, that's enough!

277
00:17:33,933 --> 00:17:35,100
I will never forgive you!

278
00:17:35,233 --> 00:17:37,600
Go home.

279
00:17:37,733 --> 00:17:38,933
What are you doing, Attorney?

280
00:17:39,067 --> 00:17:40,067
What?

281
00:17:43,833 --> 00:17:44,967
Mrs. Cruz.

282
00:17:46,100 --> 00:17:49,533
What were you thinking?
Why did you do that?

283
00:17:49,700 --> 00:17:51,867
If you went through with it,
you're done!

284
00:18:23,733 --> 00:18:24,733
What?

285
00:18:24,867 --> 00:18:26,100
Hazel did that?

286
00:18:26,700 --> 00:18:28,900
That woman's completely
lost her mind.

287
00:18:29,033 --> 00:18:30,600
Andrea, what's that?
What are you doing?

288
00:18:31,833 --> 00:18:33,133
Are you telling mom?

289
00:18:33,900 --> 00:18:34,800
No,

290
00:18:34,933 --> 00:18:36,500
but, yes, I'm telling
Attorney Yeban.

291
00:18:36,633 --> 00:18:38,167
We have to do something
about Hazel.

292
00:18:38,300 --> 00:18:39,933
Please don't.

293
00:18:40,067 --> 00:18:41,733
Things are already a mess.

294
00:18:41,867 --> 00:18:43,833
Let's not make it worse, please.

295
00:18:43,967 --> 00:18:45,200
Coleen, are you serious?

296
00:18:45,833 --> 00:18:47,033
She tried to run you over!

297
00:18:47,633 --> 00:18:49,400
Oh, what's that?
What if she'd killed you?

298
00:18:50,233 --> 00:18:52,400
She was just trying to scare me.

299
00:18:53,800 --> 00:18:56,367
Please, Andrea, let's just keep
this between us, okay?

300
00:18:58,000 --> 00:19:00,733
That's why I told you here...

301
00:19:00,867 --> 00:19:02,367
So, no one else would hear.

302
00:19:02,833 --> 00:19:04,533
No one else must know.

303
00:19:05,233 --> 00:19:07,767
Please, Andrea, don't tell mom.

304
00:19:08,767 --> 00:19:10,333
Especially not dad.

305
00:19:11,400 --> 00:19:13,900
Nothing bad happened to me, see?

306
00:19:14,033 --> 00:19:16,033
So what now, Coleen?

307
00:19:16,167 --> 00:19:17,867
You'll just wait for her
to try again?

308
00:19:19,200 --> 00:19:20,867
Wait until something bad
happens to you?

309
00:19:21,567 --> 00:19:22,933
Please, Andrea.

310
00:19:24,233 --> 00:19:25,333
Okay, fine.

311
00:19:26,800 --> 00:19:29,667
But what were you even doing
at Jessica's grave?

312
00:19:31,600 --> 00:19:32,933
You even went there
all by yourself.

313
00:19:33,967 --> 00:19:38,133
I just wanted some time
with her.

314
00:19:39,467 --> 00:19:41,433
I want to talk to her.

315
00:19:44,100 --> 00:19:46,900
I want to pour out
my thoughts to her.

316
00:19:47,967 --> 00:19:49,867
To tell her I'm sorry, Andrea.

317
00:19:50,000 --> 00:19:52,767
So maybe I could feel
a little less guilty.

318
00:19:52,900 --> 00:19:54,867
The guilt that I feel.

319
00:20:06,900 --> 00:20:08,133
Is that dad?

320
00:20:09,600 --> 00:20:11,133
What's he doing here?

321
00:20:33,400 --> 00:20:37,433
After killing you,
she now visits you.

322
00:20:38,233 --> 00:20:39,833
Calls you her sister.

323
00:20:42,267 --> 00:20:43,733
Coleen needs
to stop pretending.

324
00:20:45,233 --> 00:20:46,467
Why?

325
00:20:47,700 --> 00:20:48,900
She feels guilty?

326
00:20:51,167 --> 00:20:55,100
Then she should take
that guilt somewhere else.

327
00:20:55,233 --> 00:20:57,667
Off a rooftop, a cliff.

328
00:20:58,333 --> 00:21:00,000
A bridge, I don't care.

329
00:21:00,133 --> 00:21:01,700
If she wants, she can jump.

330
00:21:09,533 --> 00:21:10,467
Sweetie...

331
00:21:13,300 --> 00:21:14,767
Sweetie, I miss you.

332
00:21:28,167 --> 00:21:29,633
About earlier...

333
00:21:32,133 --> 00:21:33,767
why did you do that?

334
00:21:35,000 --> 00:21:37,067
You nearly gave me
a heart attack.

335
00:21:39,367 --> 00:21:41,367
Oh, please, Attorney.

336
00:21:41,500 --> 00:21:43,267
You're not having a heart attack
because of that.

337
00:21:43,433 --> 00:21:45,333
It's because of all the
junk food you've been eating.

338
00:21:48,567 --> 00:21:51,367
Mrs. Cruz, this isn't a joke.

339
00:21:52,700 --> 00:21:54,733
That was a serious offense.

340
00:21:54,867 --> 00:21:56,667
That was attempted homicide!

341
00:21:57,433 --> 00:22:00,500
Coleen could file charges
against you.

342
00:22:01,333 --> 00:22:02,900
And who's going to testify?

343
00:22:04,400 --> 00:22:05,667
The ghosts in this place?

344
00:22:07,067 --> 00:22:09,033
Mrs. Cruz, please,
don't be sarcastic.

345
00:22:09,900 --> 00:22:11,200
I'm warning you.

346
00:22:13,667 --> 00:22:16,100
Okay. Sorry.

347
00:22:17,100 --> 00:22:19,833
It won't happen again.

348
00:22:22,800 --> 00:22:24,267
Attorney...

349
00:22:24,400 --> 00:22:26,567
can you leave me alone
for a while?

350
00:22:49,267 --> 00:22:52,200
He doesn't want us
to see him grieving.

351
00:22:52,533 --> 00:22:53,667
You know, dear...

352
00:22:54,100 --> 00:22:56,033
I'm really trying
to accept that...

353
00:22:58,067 --> 00:22:59,367
that you're gone.

354
00:23:01,800 --> 00:23:03,067
<i> But it's so hard.</i>

355
00:23:05,133 --> 00:23:06,700
It's unbearably hard.

356
00:23:10,433 --> 00:23:12,500
You shouldn't have left,
Jessica.

357
00:23:15,167 --> 00:23:16,700
You shouldn't have left.

358
00:23:20,700 --> 00:23:22,633
You shouldn't have left,
sweetheart.

359
00:23:30,167 --> 00:23:31,900
I miss you so much.

360
00:23:33,600 --> 00:23:34,667
Coleen.

361
00:23:37,033 --> 00:23:38,067
Later, okay?

362
00:23:38,933 --> 00:23:41,233
Go to him later, all right?

363
00:24:06,400 --> 00:24:08,633
I'm sorry, dear!

364
00:24:09,633 --> 00:24:13,067
I'm sorry!
I'm sorry!

365
00:24:13,300 --> 00:24:14,367
Jessica, my child.

366
00:24:14,600 --> 00:24:15,933
Jessica, wait.

367
00:24:16,233 --> 00:24:17,833
Thank you for loving me back.

368
00:24:18,200 --> 00:24:20,633
Thank you for treating me
like your own child.

369
00:24:22,267 --> 00:24:23,967
Why would I ever treat you
any differently?

370
00:24:24,100 --> 00:24:26,100
Dad, please forgive me.

371
00:24:26,233 --> 00:24:27,900
Mommy and I.

372
00:24:28,033 --> 00:24:29,867
Please forgive us, Dad.

373
00:24:30,033 --> 00:24:32,133
- Jessica!
- Jessica!

374
00:24:32,267 --> 00:24:34,200
- Dad, Dad!
- Jessica.

375
00:24:34,333 --> 00:24:36,133
- Jessica, Jessica!
- Dad! Dad!

376
00:24:36,267 --> 00:24:39,567
Who here is Miss Coleen
Ruiz Cruz?

377
00:24:39,700 --> 00:24:41,300
What do you need from her?

378
00:24:42,567 --> 00:24:44,967
We're just inviting her
to the precinct.

379
00:24:45,100 --> 00:24:46,700
Do you have a warrant?
